Installing Ansible:
-------------------

=> Ansible relies on SSH and Python to do all the automation magic and so you only need to install Ansible on the control node and make sure that OpenSSH and 
	Python is installed on both the control and the managed nodes.

# Installing Ansible in CentOS 7:
---------------------------------

Step 1: Add the EPEL repository

    $ sudo yum install -y epel-release
    $ sudo yum update -y epel-release

Step 2: Install Ansible on CentOS

    $ yum install -y ansible

Step 3: Printing the Version of Ansible
    
    $ ansible --version

Step 4: How to check client connectivity

	# ansible -i ./hosts servers -m ping --user <username> --ask-pass // here inventory file is named as hosts. when executed it will use the specified username to login and prompt for 
    the ssh password

# Installing Ansible on Ubuntu:
-------------------------------

Step 1: Enable ansible-2.9 ppa repository

	# apt-add-repository --yes --update ppa:ansible/ansible-2.9

Step 2: Install Ansible on Ubuntu

	# apt-get install -y ansible
